info.description: Documentation of the SEMMED disease query web services.  Learn more about [mydisease.info](http://pending.biothings.io/semmed)
info.title: SEMMED Disease API

ids.description: multiple disease IDs separated by comma. Note that currently we only take the input ids up to 1000 maximum, the rest will be omitted. Type: string (list). Max: 1000.

200.description: A list of matching disease objects

400.description: A response indicating an improperly formatted query

post.summary: For a list of disease IDs, return the matching disease object

parameters.description: Retrieve disease objects based on ID
parameters.name: diseaseid

404.description: A response indicating an unknown disease ID

get.summary: Retrieve disease objects based on ID
Get metadata about the data available from mydisease.info
Get metadata about the data fields available from a mydisease.info chem object

parameters.description: Query string.  The detailed query syntax can be found from our [docs](http://mydisease.info).  Examples: "cancer", "primary ciliary dyskinesia", "DOID:9562"
parameters.name: q

200.description: A query response with the "hits" property

400.description: A response indicating an improperly formatted query

get.summary: Make disease queries and return matching disease hits. Supports JSONP and CORS as well.

q.description: multiple query terms separated by comma (also "+" or whitespace).  Does not support wildcard queries

scopes.description: a comma-separated list of fields as the search "scopes" (fields to search through for query term). The available "fields" that can be passed to the "scopes" parameter are listed in the **/metadata/fields** endpoint.string Default: "scopes=_id".

200.description: Query response objects with the "hits" property

400.description: A response indicating an improperly formatted query

post.summary: Make batch disease queries and return matching disease hits

callback.description: you can pass a "callback" parameter to make a JSONP call. Type: string.
callback.name: callback

dotfield.description: control the format of the returned disease object. If "true" or "1", all fields will be collapsed into a single level deep object (all nested objects will be a single level deep, using dotfield notation to signify the nested structure) Type: boolean. Default: false.
dotfield.name: dotfield

email.description: If you are regular users of our services, we encourage you to provide us with an email, so that we can better track the usage or follow up with you.
email.name: email

facet_size.description: the number of facet buckets to return in the response. Type: integer. Default: 10. Max: 1000.
facet_size.name: facet_size

facets.description: a comma-separated list of fields to return facets on.  In addition to query hits, the fields notated in "facets" will be aggregated by value and bucklet counts will be displayed in the "facets" field of the response object. Type: string (list). Default: None. Max: 1000.
facets.name: facets

fields.description: a comma-separated list of fields (in dotfield notation) used to limit the fields returned from the matching disease hit(s). The supported field names can be found from any disease object or from the /metadata/fields endpoint. If "fields=all", all available fields will be returned. Type: string (list). Default: all. Max: 1000.
fields.name: fields

format.description: controls output format of server response, currently supports: "json", "jsonld", "html". Type: string. Default: json.
format.name: format

from.description: the number of matching disease hits to skip, starting from 0.  This can be useful for paging in combination with the "size" parameter. Type: integer. Default: None.
from.name: from

prefix.description: Pass a prefix string to filter the available fields. Type: string. Default: None.
prefix.name: prefix

search.description: Pass a search term to filter the available fields. Type: string. Default: None.
search.name: search

size.description: the maximum number of matching disease hits to return per batch. Type: integer. Default: 10.
size.name: size

sort.description: the comma-separated list of fields to sort on. Prefix each with "-" for descending order, otherwise in ascending order. Default: sort by descending score.
sort.name: sort
